The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Zuari Industries Ltd, a KK Birla group company, will consider divesting its 50 per cent stake in Zuari Cements Ltd to French cement company Climents Francais SA. Zuari Cement is a 50:50 joint venture between Climents Francais of the Italcementi Group and Zuari Industries. The board will consider an offer received from the French company for purchasing the stake at a meeting scheduled to take place on May 13.

 Adidas plans to open around 60 outlets this fiscal to take the number in the country to 170. The global sports brand has posted a 97 per cent growth in its sales in the country for the year ended December 31, 2005. Adidas is spending about 8-9 per cent of its net sales on brand promotion in India and would continue the same in the coming years.

 SBI Life Insurance Company has collected a total premium of Rs 1,075 crore for the year ended March 31 and has added Rs 328 crore worth from its new business premium during the year. The company has also increased its paid-up capital by Rs 75 crore to Rs 425 crore and registered a net profit of Rs 2.2 crore last fiscal.

 Alps Industries has posted a 51 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 8.01 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31 compared with Rs 5.32 crore in the corresponding quarter. The income from operations was Rs 84.58 crore from Rs 50.05 crore, higher by about 69 per cent over the corresponding quarter. 

 Amtek Auto Ltd will raise $250 million through the issue of foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCBs) in the international market. The board has approved the issue of FCCBs, which are convertible into equity shares at a conversion price of Rs 458.64 per share. 

 Caf? Coffee Day (CCD) plans to set up highway cafes and drive through cafes to attract customers. These cafes would be set up at various petrol pumps and the company is seeking tie-ups with all leading petroleum companies in this regard, said Naresh Malhotra, director of Amalgamated Bean Coffee Trading Co, the parent company of CCD.

 Kurlon has introduced Spinekare ? a therapeutic mattress to reduce stiffness and back pain. The mattress has temperature-sensitive memory foam that can trace your changing positions in sleep quickly. The price ranges from Rs 7,000 to Rs 15,000, depending on thickness and sizes.

 Levis has launched Sykes, its college and street wear collection, in Calcutta. The collection is priced Rs 449 onwards for tops and Rs 999 onwards for bottoms.

